{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016XPpr7v4yB6FyS9WMBR9Zt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the failure patterns from the provided digest and write the feedback.md file.\n\nLooking at the 16 failures, let me group them by root cause:\n\n**1. Corrupted spillover text at start of file (no title visible in first lines)**\n- Baked Cod with Herbs: `[CORRUPTED SPILLOVER - PARTIAL TEXT FROM PREVIOUS RECIPE]` → extracted empty\n- Bigos Myśliwski: `[CORRUPTED SPILLOVER - PREVIOUS RECIPE TEXT]` → extracted empty\n- Peach Cobbler: `[CORRUPTED TEXT FROM PREVIOUS PAGE - PARTIAL RECIPE]` → extracted empty\n\n\n- Spinach and Ricotta Pie: `[CORRUPTED SPILLOVER FROM PREVIOUS PAGE]` → extracted empty\n- Zupa Koperkowa: `[CORRUPTED SPILLOVER TEXT - PARTIAL PREVIOUS RECIPE]` → extracted empty\n\nAll of these have corrupted spillover text blocking the title from appearing in the first few lines, so the extractor returns empty.\n\n**2. OCR digit-for-letter corruption in title**\n- Braised Cod with White Wine: `Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne` → extracted empty\n- Drożdże Sernik: OCR substituted digits for letters...\n\nI'm noticing a pattern where some recipes with corrupted titles extract empty, while others like Drożdże Sernik and Piernik z Śliwkami are pulling the wrong lines entirely—grabbing serving suggestions instead of actual recipe content. The digit-for-letter corruption seems to be throwing off the extraction logic inconsistently.\n\nNow looking at recipes preceded by category headers like \"FISH & SEAFOOD\" or \"VEGETABLES\"—some extract body sentences, others grab subtitles, and Ogórkowa Zupa extracts nothing despite having the title clearly marked. The header-title combination doesn't seem to be handled reliably by the current approach.\n\nFor titles split across lines like \"LEMON HERB RO45TED\\nVEGETABLES\", the extractor only catches the first line and misses the OCR corruption, so partial extraction is happening when lines need to be joined.\n\nNow looking at recipes that start mid-page without their titles present—Sweet Potato Salad and Mushroom Risotto are pulling in ingredient lines or neighboring recipe titles instead of their own headers. Meanwhile, recipes like Baked Cod with Herbs and Zupa Koperkowa return empty because the page begins with spillover text from the previous recipe and the actual title either appears later or isn't there at all.\n\nI'm also seeing OCR corruption patterns where digits replace letters in titles—Braised Cod with White Wine and Roasted Beet and Walnut Dip become unrecognizable to the extractor. And in some cases like Drożdże Sernik and Piernik z Śliwkami, the corrupted title causes the extractor to grab body text instead, returning serving instructions rather than the recipe name.\n\nWhen section headers like FISH & SEAFOOD or category metadata precede the actual recipe title, the extractor gets confused and either extracts the header itself or skips the real title entirely. Multi-line titles are also problematic—the extractor only catches fragments instead of the complete name.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":12448,"cache_read_input_tokens":10352,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":12448},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"938d7789-b3be-4402-9452-b067e080ea5e","uuid":"098cf90e-682f-4b86-be2c-23cb67336401"}
